 think about where the world will go over time.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And clearly we are investing in those kinds of areas, but we\u2019re not doing it in an unconstrained way. We\u2019re doing in a responsible way so that we can continue to drive high-quality revenue to make sure that, that we can meet our margin commitments at the same time.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Brett Huff</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">That makes sense. And as a follow-up, on bill pay you mentioned that your -- it sounds like the business model maybe evolving a little bit -- it\u2019s not as purely tied to a per trend basis maybe. Is there a -- first of all make sure I understand that right.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And second of all, is there a world in which Bill Pay stops being as a per trend revenue and becomes more, I don\u2019t know not inclusive or whatever more bundled or even a license arrangement, is that a foreseeable outcome/</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Jeff Yabuki</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Yeah so Brett, I would say that we do see a variety of different ways in which we\u2019re driving value in the bill payment business. Some of it has to do with services customization. So the ability to allow financial institutions to design experiences that make the most sense for their customers. One of things that we talked about is that spend focus is really big time around customer experience.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And you know well the traditional killer app in the digital world has been bill payment. So the ability to provide bill payment services and allow institutions to consume that the way they want to cer