 that's how we put and I would say. We're as I highlighted 40 basis points in the quarter, 20 basis points for the year and we expect that to be bigger in '15 from a headwind standpoint.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Glenn Greene</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And then just real quick on the decrease in the year-over-year corporate cost, I thought I heard you say something about lower incentive comp, which I didn't fully understand why that would be.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Tom Hirsch</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">No, no, not on the, I said lower consulting and legal cost and then in the prior year when we had an implementation of a new HR system which we have a lot of expense associated with.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Glenn Greene</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Okay. Great. Thanks a lot.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Jeff Yabuki</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Thank you.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong>Operator</strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Our last question comes from Kartik Mehta. Your line is open of Northcoast Research.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Kartik Mehta</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Thanks. Jeff, you talked about gaining market share on the bill payment side, I am wondering is the competitive environment changing or what are the drivers that for you to be able to gain that market share?</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Jeff Yabuki</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">I think what we said is we had our strongest sales quarter in the fourth quarter since 2012 when we had somewhere north of 300 wins for the year, which is pretty consistent with what we've seen going for the last several years. So I would say its two fold.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">It is first and foremost having what we believe is the best solution in the market and that's especially important as speed becomes more and more important to consumer. So the ability to link up the certainly the -- again we think is the best product in the market with some of our solutions such as PEP+ which are going to help today enable real time.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And they've got a big opportunity and a big differentiator and then secondly, the continuing ability to deliver that into our account processing base, which a you know is somewhere in the area of 5,000 financial institutions. So is really the combination of those two that's creating the success.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Kartik Mehta</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And then just a question Jeff may be a business that's been forgotten or not talked about, the check processing business and as you see checks declined, are there opportunities for you out there and our client base or outside your client base to when that business and potentially help the check processing business these banks come under pressure as their volumes are declining?</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Jeff Yabuki</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">The theoretic answer is yes. I would say that over time, there have been several different junctures where we believed that given the financial pressures that there would be motivation to outsource that solution.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And today, we've had discussions, but we frankly haven't seen a lot of movement in that space and I am sure there are a variety of reasons why, but for now, we certainly are counting on that happening when we think about forward revenue growth.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">If it happens that's great, but it's certainly in our part it's not an important part of our growth formula moving forward.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Kartik Mehta</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">And then Jeff, just a last question, any benefits or hurdles from the regulator environment that could help you grow revenue or when additional market share from others?</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Jeff Yabuki</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">I there is a general -- there is a general quote \u201cbenefit in the market\u201d because of the level of regulatory scrutiny and pressure, which is causing institutions to take a good look at how they spend and are they getting the most or they getting the optimal value for that spend.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">I would say that's a more systemic benefit and that the providers themselves are generally equal on that front.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"answer\">Mark Ernst</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">There probably are a few of our product lines that are disproportionally benefitting from the regulatory pressure. We talked about the opportunity in lending, which has a strong kind of regulatory under current to the changes that we've seen in that market.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong><span class=\"question\">Kartik Mehta</span></strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">All right, thanks Mark; thanks Jeff. Appreciate it.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong>Jeff Yabuki</strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Absolutely. Thanks everyone for joining us this afternoon. I know we went a little bit longer than we typically do, but we appreciate your support. If you have any further questions, please don't hesitate to contact our investor relations team. Have a good evening.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\"><strong>Operator</strong></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible no-summary-bullets\">Thank you for your participation in today's call. You may now disconnect.</p>", "twitContent": "$FI - Fiserv's (FISV) CEO Jeff Yabuki on Q4 2014 Results - Earnings Call Transcript. https://seekingalpha.com/article/2881366-fiservs-fisv-ceo-jeff-yabuki-on-q4-2014-results-earnings-call-transcript?source=tweet ", "innerMarketing": null, "marketingBullet": "", "isReit": false, "videoData": null, "marketingBulletVariant": null, "marketingBio": null}, "relationships": {"author": {"data": {"id": "44211", "type": "author"}}, "sentiments": {"data": []}, "primaryTickers": {"data": [{"id": "1224", "type": "tag"}]}, "secondaryTickers": {"data": []}, "otherTags": {"data": [{"id": "96991", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "17933", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "49", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "326", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "17945", "type": "tag"}]}, "coAuthors": {"data": []}, "presentations": {"data": []}, "updates": {"data": []}, "corrections": {"data": []}}, "